1 week after the nuclear bombing of Racoon City the Umbrella Corporation sends another special force into the hive to find the antidote against the T-Virus. But the zombies down there are still alive and hungry...

Here's my next zm-map after zm_piranesi and zm_Fidlers-Green. The story is centered around the underground labor called the hive of the Resident Evil movie. It contains the trainyard, the labs, the laserroom, the office and some warehouses. 

There are some scripted events and alot of shock moments build in. Also some weird stuff was going on down there beside the T-Virus, so give it a shot and enjoy the show :)

ps: still looking for a server to test my maps ;) add Euerfeldi in steam for infos

This was the first map i had ever made. I wasn't very creative and didn't know where to start, so i decided i'd just remake q2dm1 from Quake 2. That was my favourite game, so why not? Map has a bunch of secrets, hold spots, and cade spots. It's not the greatest map, and i didn't make it very well at all. I was just procrastinating posting it here. Originally i had the plan of getting rid of the Plaguefest sign in one of the secrets and make a seperate release for the public, but it doesn't really matter. If you need to change it on your own, just message me for the VMF and i'll gladly give it to you.

Also, i don't know why the file size is so big, i probably used a rediculous model or didn't scale down custom textures.

Known Bugs:
- Can get stuck in some displacements
- Water can reflect weird sometimes (cubemaps issue i think), couldn't figure out why at the time

Pretty straightforward map design, based off of one I did a year back for the CSSMC zombie server. Players are spawned in a large crater, and there are movable boxes scattered everywhere.

 (In the original, there was a crane overlooking the map, and was called "dayoff"; just a crane worker goofing off, was the "backstory)

There is also, as in the original, a pretty decent concrete "structure" that can be defended, or attacked, with comparitive ease. Dead simple game play, but if it works as well as the original did, it'll be a hoot to play in a full server. Enjoy :)

And please notify me if your server plans on using this or any other map I make. It doesnt matter if you do or not, but I'd sure like to see it in action :).

Made for the .:{420}:. Zombie Mod Server. IP - 8.6.8.175:27015

LIST OF CHANGES AND ADDITIONS.
-Added 4 zombie launchers.  Two for each spawn.  ONLY TWO ARE RECOMMENDED FOR HUMANS.  THE OTHER ONE ALWAYS LEADS TO DEATH.
-Redesigned the structure on the CT side cosmetically.  Took out vents and added another perch.
-Enlarged inside hideout of T structure making it alittle more possible for zombies, also added glass rooms outside of there.  Outside wall of the glass will eventually break if shot too much.
-Added breakable openings to the large rooms on the big building.
-Lowered upper blocks and platforms to be a tad easier for zombies.
-Added two more hovering platforms with teleports leading to them.  Locations of the teleports are hidden, but not too hard to figure out.
-Took out second floor wrap around.  Just wasted space.
-Added a couple more boxes to truck area.
-Doubled damage of the killing floor so zombies die faster.
-Turtles strewn about the map.  Why?  Cause I can.

PLEASE REPORT ANY BUGS.

-For some reason the launcher that goes over the trucks on the T side launches really far, so more control is needed on that, but it's still usable.

For a little while, this map stayed exclusive to the Plaguefest server while i was figuring everything out. Anyone who leaked the map didn't have a working version for their server, since it didn't apply the surf settings how it regularly should have. I did a lot of balancing over time on this, and got this to a working, public state. This is by far not the best surf map, in fact, it doesn't have a whole lot of surf at all. It's basically just do a quick surf to the location you want to go and hold it.

This surf n cade style map was presented as an idea on the Plaguefest forums, but nobody had taken up the idea. Eventually after being bugged enough, i gave in and created this. Mind you, i had never really ever played surf, so i was terrible at it and didn't really know all the mechanics to surfing. For what it is, it's definitely worth giving it a try. It even has a Cade Only location for players who aren't good at surfing or can't at all.

There is only 1 secret, and it is just music. 4 different songs, 1 troll song that you need noclip to access. Songs are:

Wolfgang Gartner - Redline

Zedd - Push Play

Noisecontrollers - Unite

Men Without Hats - Safety Dance

Hello fpsbanana and thanks for checking out my map!
I havn't been too active on fpsbanana lately, mostly because of school and some other things, but I hope I can get more active in the future!

About the map, well it is an old map that I started working on about 1 year ago since I thought It would be cool to do a subway for some reason. I never planned to release it, but since it turned out pretty good I decided that there maybe was someone out there who would like it!
However since I never planned on releasing it I never made the layout of the map "optimizable" so I spent some time trying to figure out how I could make it more fps-friendly. 

I consider the map complete now, I have even had 3 betas here on fpsbanana for feedback about the gameplay. I did however not get that much feedback on the gameplay so I am not sure how it is yet, since I havnt been able to test it with zombiemod myself. I dont really have any more time to spend on this map, so it would be nice of you to tell me what the gameplay is like asap.

The map is complete with Cubemaps, Playerclips, Soundscapes and all that good stuff, theres even 64 spawns in it. I have also added a radar overview as you asked for in the betas.
This map also features Color Correction, so make sure you have it enabled in your video options since it makes the map look over 9000 times better!

As I said, I can make minor changes to the map, but tell me as soon as possible since I dont really wanna spend more time on it hehe.


Here's a link to my steam-profile as you requested ;) 
http://steamcommunity.com/profiles/76561197992346412

---BETA---
